Set Up Service Cloud Basics Design and Optimize the Agent Experience Deflect Cases with Self-Service Add Service Cloud Channels Set Up Routing and Rules Build AI Solutions with Einstein for Service Einstein Article Recommendations Einstein Bots Einstein Classification Apps Einstein Conversation Mining Einstein Grounding Einstein Knowledge Creation Einstein Replies Einstein Service Replies Einstein Service Replies for Chat Einstein Service Replies for Email Einstein Reply Recommendations Einstein Work Summaries Einstein and Data Usage in Service Track Service Metrics and Manage Your Team Send Surveys with Feedback Management Deliver Field Service Provide Ethical Customer Service More Service Cloud Features

You are here: Salesforce Help Docs Service Cloud Einstein Service Replies Increase customer satisfaction and reduce agent handling time with AI-generated replies. Einstein can generate replies during a customer chat. Or, draft and send emails based on recommended Knowledge articles, directly from the Case page.

Step 1. Check your Einstein readiness. See whether you meet the license and edition requirements. If you aren’t sure, contact your Salesforce account executive to get started.
 
Turn on Einstein generative AI. Set up Salesforce Knowledge. For the best results, we recommend starting with at least 10 articles. Set up Service AI Grounding. (Optional) Set up Article Recommendations.

Step 2. Set up the prerequisites. Make sure you’ve completed these steps.

Step 3. Set up Service Replies. To get started, turn on replies. You can use Service Replies in messaging, chat and email conversations. Then, give your agents a permission set so they can use replies.

Step 4. Get acquainted with Service Replies in the console. For chat and messaging sessions, see how agents select, edit, and post replies. Einstein even shows you whether replies are based on conversation context or your knowledge articles. For email, see how agents select an article for Einstein to draft a reply and then edit and send it to customers all from the case page.

Step 5. Share insights from your data. Based on data from your Salesforce org, share insights with your team using Einstein Generative AI and Feedback Data reports, and the Audit Trail.
title: Setting Up and Using Service Cloud with Einstein
